race.comment: Looking to bet around the favourite in the first of our Group Ones, the Thousand Guineas. GETTA GOOD FEELING (4) won the Edward Manifold last start and would've been something licked if she didn't, getting clear air late and dashing up strongly. Drawn to effect, double figures here looks appealing. CHATEAU EZE (11) won dominantly at Benalla on debut and measured up well in a fast race here in the Jim Moloney over 1400m. She'll relish the mile now and is another at big odds. It's hard to knock the even-money favourite APOCALYPTIC (1) who has swept the princess series in Sydney, culminating with an effortless victory in the G1 Flight Stakes last time. She did get every favour sitting on a slow speed but it was a soft win and she maps ideally. OLE DANCER (3) is crying out for a mile, tipping she turns the tables on FERIVIA (2) from the Prelude and can win from the good gate.
